Sands of Time- life is a lot like a sand dune. We get broken down, built back up, and we change and evolve through time shaped by the forces around us. I hit a milestone today I never imagined possible when I started photography four years ago. I have never stopped learning, shifting and growing with help from family and the community of creatives on IG. Thank from the bottom of my heart for your support, inspiration, advice, wisdom, and comments.

node.text:
May the sun guide your way through the many layers of life. 
•••••
Thanks to Julianna @julitmart for the beautiful view. 
•
...goodbye summer...ok, I know that we have a couple more weeks of summer left - but with schools starting again (and a husband who is a professor) - it always feels to me like Labor Day weekend is the end of summer...

One thing that I have enjoyed over the last year and a half is exploring some regions of the East Coast more in depth. We had to cancel 2 major trips because of the pandemic. But I enjoyed our alternate plans in places like the New River Gorge (even  before it was a National Park 😊 ) and Charleston 🌴. My husband and I spent 4 years in NC in our 20s ( post-doc years) and we had loved going into the mountains. I have thoroughly enjoyed the multiple trips I have been to take to that region in the past year and a half - I have fallen in love with those mountains all over again. Actually. I am currently quite obsessed with that region. There is nothing quite like the layers of the the southern Appalachian Mountains ! 🌄

Have a great weekend ! ( photo is from another sunset hike in the NC mountains a few weeks ago).
